-- French Stocks Advance: Eiffage, LVMH, Rhodia Increase as Technip Declines
-- Adria Cimino
-- 2010-06-17T10:37:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/french-stocks-fluctuate-eiffage-lvmh-rhodia-gain-as-technip-declines.html

          
          
             France’s  CAC 40 Index  rose 30.51, or
0.8 percent, to 3,706.44 at 12:21 p.m. in Paris.  The SBF 120
Index  also gained 0.8 percent.  
 The CAC 40 followed European shares higher, after Spain
sold 3 billion euros ($3.7 billion) of 10-year bonds and 479.2
million euros of 30-year debt at auction today. The Treasury had
planned to sell a maximum of 3.5 billion euros today.  
 Stocks most sensitive to economic growth led gains. Societe
Generale SA, France’s second-biggest bank by market value,
rallied 3.4 percent to 37.39 euros. Cie. de Saint-Gobain,
Europe’s biggest supplier of building materials, advanced 1.7
percent to 34.27 euros. Alcatel-Lucent SA, the largest French
telecommunications equipment maker, increased 1.7 percent to
2.28 euros.  
 The following shares rose or fell in Paris. Stock symbols
are in parentheses.  
 Cegid Group SA  (CGD FP) climbed 2.2 percent to 21.99 euros,
gaining for a seventh day. The developer of enterprise business
systems said it acquired human-resources services group Vedior
Front RH for an undisclosed price.  
 Eiffage SA  (FGR FP) surged 12 percent to 40.56 euros for
its biggest gain since March 2007. Eiffage and Macquarie Group
Ltd. confirmed the purchase of a stake in their APRR toll-road
venture. Earlier, Les Echos reported that the companies agreed
to pay 854 million euros ($1.05 billion) to raise their stake in
APRR to 95 percent from 81.48 percent.  
 Eramet SA  (ERA FP) advanced 3.9 percent to 230.50 euros,
erasing yesterday’s loss. The operator of the world’s largest
ferronickel plant agreed “in principle” to offer a stake in
the company to Gabon and give the state an increased holding in
their joint venture manganese mine in the country.  
 Imerys SA  (NK FP), a minerals processor, jumped 8.2 percent
to 45.94 euros for its biggest increase in five weeks. Cheuvreux
raised its recommendation on the stock to “outperform” from
“underperform.”  
 LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA  (MC FP) added 1.1
percent to 93.14 euros, gaining for a second day. The company
will re-open Paris’s historic Samaritaine department store with
offices and a luxury hotel, Les Echos reported, citing the
store’s Chief Executive Officer Philippe de Beauvoir.  
 Rhodia SA  (RHA FP) advanced 4.2 percent to 14.97 euros,
gaining for a sixth day. The French maker of plastics and
perfume ingredients is planning to acquire Feixiang Chemicals to
expand its presence in Asia. The price of the Chinese producer
of surfactants and amines is based on an enterprise value of
$489 million and the deal is expected to be completed in the
second half of 2010, the Paris-based company said.  
